%% Merge Conflict Resolution Process
%% Shows step-by-step conflict resolution

graph TB
    Start([Two developers editing<br/>same file]) --> Dev1[Developer 1<br/>edits index.html<br/>line 10: 'Hello World']
    Start --> Dev2[Developer 2<br/>edits index.html<br/>line 10: 'Kumusta Mundo']
    
    Dev1 --> Commit1[Developer 1<br/>commits & pushes first]
    Dev2 --> Commit2[Developer 2<br/>commits & tries to push]
    
    Commit1 --> Remote[GitHub Repository<br/>line 10: 'Hello World']
    Commit2 --> Pull[Developer 2:<br/>git pull origin main]
    
    Remote --> Pull
    Pull --> Conflict{Merge Conflict!}
    
    Conflict --> VSCode[Open in VS Code<br/>See conflict markers]
    VSCode --> Markers["<<<<<<< HEAD<br/>Hello World<br/>=======<br/>Kumusta Mundo<br/>>>>>>>> incoming"]
    
    Markers --> Choose{Choose resolution}
    Choose --> |Keep current| Option1[Accept Current Change]
    Choose --> |Keep incoming| Option2[Accept Incoming Change]
    Choose --> |Keep both| Option3[Accept Both Changes]
    Choose --> |Manual edit| Option4[Edit manually]
    
    Option1 --> Resolve[Resolved:<br/>'Hello World']
    Option2 --> Resolve2[Resolved:<br/>'Kumusta Mundo']
    Option3 --> Resolve3[Resolved:<br/>'Hello World<br/>Kumusta Mundo']
    Option4 --> Resolve4[Resolved:<br/>'Hello World / Kumusta Mundo']
    
    Resolve --> Stage[git add index.html]
    Resolve2 --> Stage
    Resolve3 --> Stage
    Resolve4 --> Stage
    
    Stage --> CommitMerge[git commit -m<br/>'Resolve merge conflict']
    CommitMerge --> PushFinal[git push origin main]
    PushFinal --> Done([Conflict Resolved!<br/>Changes merged])
    
    style Start fill:#ffebee
    style Conflict fill:#ff6b6b,color:#fff
    style VSCode fill:#e3f2fd
    style Choose fill:#fff9e6
    style Option1 fill:#e8f5e9
    style Option2 fill:#e8f5e9
    style Option3 fill:#e8f5e9
    style Option4 fill:#e8f5e9
    style Done fill:#c8e6c9

